static.solution:
\displaystyle \int u^n du = \frac{u^{n+1}}{n+1}:
\parbox{0.4\textwidth}{

\ \begin{aligned}
\int_{1}^{7} \frac 1 {x^2} dx  \amp  = \int_{1}^{7} x^{-2} dx \\\\ 
\amp  =	\left (-1)x^{-1} \right|_{1}^{7} = \left \frac{-1}{x} \right|_{1}^{7}	\\\\
\amp  =	\frac{-1}{7} - \frac{-1}{1}	= \frac 1 {1} - \frac 1 {7} = 0.857143
\end{aligned} }

p.me:
\begin{aligned}
\int_{4}^{5} (2 x + 7) dx \amp=  2 \int_{4}^{5} x\, dx + 7 \int_{4}^{5} dx\\
 \amp=  2 \left( \left. \frac{x^2}{2} \right|_{4}^{5} \right)
                      + 7 \left( \left. x \right|_{4}^{5} \right)\\
 \amp=  2 \left( \frac{5^2}{2} - \frac{4^2}{2} \right)
                      + 7 \left( 5 - 4 \right) = {16}
\end{aligned}

